      <div class="page-hero__card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Our story</div>
        <h1>About Little Eyes International</h1>
        <p>
          Little Eyes International is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization based in Arizona. As pediatric
          eye care providers, our goal is to deliver optical, clinical, and surgical eye care services to
          underserved children in both Arizona and Sonora, Mexico. Our mission is to prevent and treat
          childhood blindness for patients of all socioeconomic backgrounds.
        </p>
        <p>
          Little Eyes International was founded in July 2021 by pediatric ophthalmologists Dr. Laura Kueny
          and Dr. Patrick Burke. In 2019, Dr. Kueny and Dr. Burke began volunteering with a Lions Club mobile
          unit to reach children in rural Arizona and provide free eye care services. Unfortunately, this
          program was suspended during the COVID-19 pandemic. At that time, access to pediatric ophthalmology
          in Arizona was limited to just two cities: Tucson and Phoenix. The pandemic also created additional
          barriers for families in Mexico who relied on crossing the border for medical care. As a result,
          many families were left without access to treatment or faced significant travel burdens to receive care.
        </p>
        <p>
          In September 2021, Little Eyes International partnered with Rocky Point Medical Center in Puerto
          Pe&#241;asco, Sonora, Mexico. Through this collaboration, the organization has provided pediatric eye
          clinics, vision screenings, and free prescription eyeglasses to children in need.
        </p>
        <p>
          In June 2025, Little Eyes International expanded its impact by partnering with Dr. Josh Leonard of
          Complete Vision Care to deliver mobile pediatric eye clinics across Arizona, increasing access for
          uninsured and underinsured students.
        </p>
        <p>
          At Little Eyes International, we are committed to expanding access to pediatric eye care because
          every child deserves to see clearly.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary back-btn" href="/">&#8592; Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

